This paper is likely to belong to the category of "Computation and Language" (cs.CL) as it proposes a new attention network for the decoder part of the neural Transformer to improve the decoding speed in machine translation tasks. It also involves natural language processing and language modeling. 

It could also belong to "Machine Learning" (cs.LG) as it involves the development of a new neural network architecture to improve the performance of machine translation models. 

"Artificial Intelligence" (cs.AI) is another likely category as the paper proposes a new approach to improve the efficiency of machine translation models, which is a key area of research in AI. 

"Neural and Evolutionary Computing" (cs.NE) is also a possible category as the paper involves the use of neural networks to improve the performance of machine translation models. 

Finally, "Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition" (cs.CV) is a less likely category, but still possible as the paper involves the development of a new attention network architecture, which is a key component in many computer vision tasks such as image captioning and object recognition.
